seeing "analyses" about user profitability on @pumpdotfun make a comeback

Here’s why you shouldn't only ignore the FUD, but why this data is BULLISH for onchain trading as a whole https://t.co/6mSZPB7e64

there are many issues with this "analysis"

FIRST and foremost, buying coins after they have already bonded to Raydium is NOT included when calculating your pnl

this means that if you bought Fartcoin at $200k and sold today (a return of over 4,000x), your pnl would be $0

weird.

if they actually tried the platform or spoke to users they'd know that most of the gains are made AFTER a coin bonds

therefore, it's likely that the true number of profitable and extremely profitable wallets is an order of magnitude LARGER than exhibited

second, they don't take unrealized profit into account

some of the most profitable wallets are those that have deep conviction in bags that they picked up very early on

that means that if you bought $PNUT at $40k on pump fun and held to this day, your pnl would be NEGATIVE

🤦‍♂️

third, they claim that there are over 13m traders on the platform, a massive share of which have negative pnl's

again, if you spent a day in the trenches you'd know that this is false. there are tons of non-human wallets that interact with the protocol: bots, AI agents, etc.
fun fact: ~30% of all wallets only ever place a single trade - a sell order. I'll let you figure out how that's possible, but it's certainly not human activity

in conclusion: don't listen to engagement farmers. they coordinate FUD when the market crashes so disgruntled traders engage with their content
